19
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,770
[Main Conference Room]
the allergic symptoms of Alteplase.

20
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:53,740
R&D Department,

21
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,490
any further questions?

22
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:57,900
I have no issues here.

23
00:01:58,150 --> 00:02:00,490
But reports involving adverse reactions

24
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,660
still need final confirmation

25
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,770
from PV.

26
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,850
It's already been verified.

27
00:02:09,590 --> 00:02:10,850
After receiving an intravenous injection

28
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:11,940
of 8mg Alteplase,

29
00:02:12,310 --> 00:02:14,060
followed by a 50-minute infusion,

30
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,260
the subject experienced a severe allergic reaction.

31
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,570
All right.

32
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,170
Since there are no objections,

33
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:20,730
we can officially submit

34
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,260
the marketing application for SA-0988.

35
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,220
I'm not finished yet.

36
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,290
The subject

37
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:28,980
did use Alteplase that day,

38
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,500
and did experience an allergic reaction.

39
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,940
But this was the first time he used this drug.

40
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:35,130
So the claim of hiding the allergy history

41
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,690
doesn't hold up.

42
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,730
Someone

43
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,170
tried to use this statement

44
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,980
to revoke the subject's

45
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:43,850
trial qualification.

46
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,340
This was meant to invalidate his trial data,

47
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,340
thus making everyone overlook

48
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,290
a more serious issue.

49
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,540
That is, SA-0988

50
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,610
may be linked

51
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:54,730
to the subject's sudden cerebral infarction.

52
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:56,980
The subject

53
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:58,660
had no history of cerebral infarction.

54
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,100
But four hours

55
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:01,980
after using SA-0988,

56
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,290
he suffered a cerebral infarction.

57
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,220
This case,

58
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,170
according to the regulations,

59
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,130
must be classified

60
00:03:06,150 --> 00:03:06,730
as a SUSAR

61
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,170
and reported.

62
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,610
So,

63
00:03:08,630 --> 00:03:09,340
to invalidate this case

64
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:09,940
as a SUSAR,

65
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,060
the only way

66
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:15,100
is to revoke the subject's qualification.

67
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:25,220
Jiang Jiaqi, what do you mean?

68
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,100
Are you questioning

69
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:29,730
the authenticity of this statement?

70
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,130
When our company received this statement,

71
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,010
it's my responsibility

72
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:33,980
to take it seriously.

73
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:35,380
Who knows

74
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,610
why he had to write this statement?

75
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,290
Do you want me to spell it out for you?

76
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,170
Director Jiang,

77
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,940
I'm very clear in my mind

78
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,380
how much effort

79
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,780
everyone at the company

80
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:45,780
has put into SA-0988.

81
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:47,170
So I want to ask everyone,

82
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,730
who doesn't know how important safety is?

83
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:53,340
But medical development

84
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,540
and the advancement of drugs

85
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,610
have always come

86
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:57,380
with risks.

87
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,660
So many Alzheimer's patients

88
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,940
in our country

89
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,290
are waiting for medication.

90
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:03,500
Their condition

91
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:05,410
continues to worsen day by day.

92
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,170
The earlier it's approved,

93
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,010
the sooner

94
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:08,850
we can help them

95
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:10,060
delay the progression of their disease,

96
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:10,980
and alleviate their suffering.

97
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,890
We have such a large trial base.

98
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:16,220
Why should we focus

99
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,730
on such a small probability

100
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,540
of adverse reaction?

101
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,100
I believe we can

102
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,980
push SA-0988 to market quickly,

103
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,340
and then continue to optimize it.

104
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:27,980
Director Jiang,

105
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,370
if this is because

106
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:30,540
of your personal emotions,

107
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,020
I must remind you,

108
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,170
don't let them affect your work.

109
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:42,250
Do you know

110
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:43,340
what the subject told me?

111
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,170
If it's his fault

112
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:48,220
that this drug won't make it to market,

113
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:50,810
